children.subject: There is a piazza group that you will be able to join if you attend our orientation and fill out the contract. Once you fill out the contract, you will be able to choose lab times and get updates through the piazza. The interest form gives us a way to send out a first wave of emails to those who are interested.

Has the email regarding the timings for the orientation been sent? If so, unfortunately I was unable to receive it.

I'm only worried since 61A's orientation is pretty soon and I've yet to find out when 61B's orientation is.

Of course, if you have yet to send the details regarding the orientation, sorry to bother you. You can ignore this message.
The time is posted on the application. We will be in HP auditorium this Saturday and will have the orientation split into two halves (2:30-3:30, 3:30-4:30) in order to accommodate everyone.

Is there a Piazza group for 61B AI like there is for 61A? Secondly, is there a similar orientation process? If not, when and where exactly will we be signing up contract for the 61B AI position (since the interest form was non-binding)?

history.content:
Hello there!

As we dive into the new school year, we're looking forward to a great semester of CS 61B and need academic interns (formerly, lab assistants) to support students!

As an academic intern you will have the chance to help students the way you were helped in CS 61B by working together with them through lab assignments and homeworks during office hours and lab. Through your semester as an academic intern, you'll gain a deeper understanding of the course material as well as valuable experience toward becoming a tutor or TA. Additionally, you will receive P/NP units when you help for a minimum of 3 hours per week with a few additional requirements.

If you’re interested, please fill out the interest form here! Academic interning starts Monday, September 2 during the second week of instruction.

CS 61B Staff
